## Phase 1 — Paperwork Formalism & Deterministic Inspections
**(ACTIVE / Mostly Complete)**

> **Purpose:** Make sloppy paperwork detectable — without punishment.

### What Is Already Implemented

#### Document Formalism
- Required fields per document type (`SURFACE_COMPLIANCE_RULES`)
- Cargo line validation
- Container metadata validation
- Action-scoped requirements (`ENTRY_CLEARANCE`, `SELL_CARGO_LEGAL`)
- Immutable edit-event evidence model

#### Deterministic Inspection Infrastructure
- Deterministic customs pressure calculation
- Deterministic entry jurisdiction selection:
  - highest-pressure location in system
  - lexicographic tie-break
- Deterministic inspection roll:
  - seeded by `(system_id, location_id, action, time_tick)`
  - randomness affects **whether**, never **what**

#### Active Inspection Execution
- `Customs.run_entry_check()` exists
- `GameState.run_customs_inspection()`:
  - evaluates evidence
  - produces explainable classification
  - logs findings
  - emits completion signals
- No cargo, credit, or document mutation occurs as a result

> **Note:** Level 1 inspections are already live in code, even if not fully wired to all triggers yet.

### What Phase 1 Explicitly Does *Not* Do

- No fines
- No cargo denial
- No travel blocking
- No reputation effects
- No Port Authority simulation

---

## Phase 1.5 — Inspection Trigger Completion (NEXT)

> **Purpose:** Ensure inspections occur *only* at correct player-action boundaries.

### Required Wiring

| Trigger | Status | Required Action |
| --- | --- | --- |
| System entry clearance | Partially wired | Ensure `Customs.run_entry_check()` fires on actual system arrival |
| Legal cargo sale | Over-eager | Gate inspection behind pressure + deterministic roll |
| Port departure clearance | Missing | Add departure-triggered inspection hook |

### Design Rules (Non-Negotiable)

- All triggers must:
  - be player-action boundaries
  - use deterministic rolls
  - be pressure-gated
- No trigger may:
  - mutate cargo
  - mutate credits
  - destroy documents
  - block player action

### Outcome

- Inspections feel consistent and fair
- Logs match player expectations
- No gameplay punishment yet

➡️ **This phase is the current focus of the epic.**

